<subSubSection id="C33A1BD9FFD0FF9BFF1DFB913DA3FB16" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9F4852FFD0FF9BFF1DFB913C1AFB58" blockId="19.[151,1437,640,1478]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFF1DFB913B6FFBA1" bold="true" box="[198,512,1103,1129]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD0FF9BFDC6FB8E3A09FBA1" authorityName="Leme &amp; Kollmann" authorityYear="2007" box="[541,870,1104,1129]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudovagans">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFDC6FB8E3A09FBA1" box="[541,870,1104,1129]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Orthophytum pseudovagans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from Águia Branca county in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49E486B0FFD0FF9BFF28FBA838F2FB58" box="[243,413,1142,1168]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, where it grows on rocky outcrops in the Atlantic rain forests at ca 
<quantity id="4CD8E5B7FFD0FF9BFB6BFBA83D95FB58" box="[1200,1274,1142,1168]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="m" value="250.0">250 m</quantity>
elevation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9F4852FFD0FF9BFF1DFB433DA3FB16" blockId="19.[151,1437,640,1478]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFF1DFB433B73FB7F" bold="true" box="[198,540,1181,1207]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">IUCN conservation status:</emphasis>
—DD. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD0FF9BFDA3FB433AA8FB7E" authorityName="Leme &amp; Kollmann" authorityYear="2007" box="[632,967,1181,1206]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudovagans">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFDA3FB433AA8FB7E" box="[632,967,1181,1206]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Orthophytum pseudovagans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
still lacks sufficient distribution data, because it was discovered only recently and is currently known only from the 
<typeStatus id="549BF6F0FFD0FF9BFBF1FB1A3D33FB16" box="[1066,1116,1220,1246]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33A1BD9FFD0FF9BFF1DFB343AE8FA0E" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9F4852FFD0FF9BFF1DFB343BDAFA9A" blockId="19.[151,1437,640,1478]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFF1DFB343838FACC" bold="true" box="[198,343,1258,1284]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Comments:</emphasis>
—According to Leme &amp; Kollmann (2007), 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD0FF9BFC87FB353D48FACC" authorityName="Leme &amp; Kollmann" authorityYear="2007" box="[860,1063,1259,1284]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudovagans">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFC87FB353D48FACC" box="[860,1063,1259,1284]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">O. pseudovagans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms the ' 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD0FF9BFB75FB353C6EFACC" authorityName="Foster" authorityYear="1960" box="[1198,1281,1259,1284]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vagans">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFB75FB353C6EFACC" box="[1198,1281,1259,1284]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">vagans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subcomplex' together with 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD0FF9BFEE3FACF3B10FAE3" authority="Foster (1960: 59)" authorityName="Foster" authorityPageNumber="59" authorityYear="1960" box="[312,639,1297,1323]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vagans">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFEE3FACF38C0FAE2" box="[312,431,1297,1322]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">O. vagans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB135A3FFD0FF9BFE6EFACF3B10FAE3" author="Foster, M. B." box="[437,639,1297,1323]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="59 - 60" refId="ref11960" refString="Foster, M. B. (1960) A wandering Orthophytum. Bulletin of the Bromeliad Society 10: 59 - 60." type="journal article" year="1960">Foster (1960: 59)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD0FF9BFD6CFACF3D62FAE3" authority="Leme (2004 b: 72)" authorityName="Leme" authorityPageNumber="72" authorityYear="2004" box="[695,1037,1297,1323]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zanonii">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFD6CFACF3A5EFAE2" box="[695,817,1297,1322]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">O. zanonii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB135A3FFD0FF9BFCECFACF3D62FAE3" author="Leme, E. M. C." box="[823,1037,1297,1323]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="66 - 74" refId="ref12173" refString="Leme, E. M. C. (2004 b) Studies on Orthophytum - Part II: Two new scapeless species. Journal of the Bromeliad Society 54: 66 - 74." type="journal article" year="2004">Leme (2004b: 72)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Long stems and obtuse–cucullate petal apices characterize this group of species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9F4852FFD0FF9BFF1DFA813AE8FA0E" blockId="19.[151,1437,640,1478]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD0FF9BFF1DFA813B7EFAB0" authorityName="Leme &amp; Kollmann" authorityYear="2007" box="[198,529,1375,1400]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pseudovagans">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFF1DFA813B7EFAB0" box="[198,529,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Orthophytum pseudovagans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD0FF9BFD6BFA813A47FAB0" authorityName="Foster" authorityYear="1960" box="[688,808,1375,1400]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vagans">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFD6BFA813A47FAB0" box="[688,808,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">O. vagans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly by its compound (vs. simple) inflorescences. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2033D1FFD0FF9BFE91FA5B38A7FA56" box="[330,456,1413,1438]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Orthophytum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zanonii">
<emphasis id="B9549440FFD0FF9BFE91FA5B38A7FA56" box="[330,456,1413,1438]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">O. zanonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by longer leaf blades (
<quantity id="4CD8E5B7FFD0FF9BFD05FA5B3A38FA57" box="[734,855,1413,1439]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="cm" value="42.5" valueMax="55.0" valueMin="30.0">30–55 cm</quantity>
vs. 12–14.6), which are glabrous, bright green–spotted and red at the base (vs. lepidote and concolorous green).
</paragraph>
